parameters:
"There was a swarm of monsters on the mountain past this
cave. I was just on my way back from subduing them."
"What about you, Suelle? Why are you in a place like this?"
"I wanted some materials to make a new device."

With that, Suelle showed the ore he had been collecting
until just before.
"If you had told me, I would have come with you."

"Besides, this place was supposed to be relatively safe, so
I thought it would be no problem even alone."

Tina also looked at the monster she had defeated earlier
upon hearing Suelle's words.

"This monster, a Wolfen, right? They're not supposed to be
in a place like this."

The monster Tina had defeated was one that normally required
a party of several people to subdue. It was not the kind of
monster that should be in a cave near town.
"Maybe something has happened to the ecosystem balance."

"But really, thank goodness. As expected of a member of
Lucent, the party that defeated the Demon Lord."

What Suelle said was true. Tina was one of the members who
defeated the Demon Lord.

However, Tina had a difficult expression on her face at
Suelle's words.

"You always talk as if it's someone else's business, but
weren't you also one of those members?"
Indeed, Suelle himself was also one of those heroic members.

Even so, Suelle himself doesn't have the same combat ability
as Tina.
"Even though I'm a member, I'm just an artificer."

An artificer refers to items, weapons, and armor that
utilize the spell formulas of this world. They usually come
in various forms and have a wide range of effects depending
on their purpose.
For example, Tina also has a ring made by Suelle.

This ring is a special artificer that transforms into a
sword when Tina pours her power into it.

Artificers play an important role in battle, and those who
develop, adjust, modify, and repair them are called
artificers.

Therefore, when embarking on a long journey, regardless of
being a party of heroes, the role of an artificer is
essential to the party.

"I was just providing support with the artificers; all the
fighting was done by Tina Onee-san and the others."
Tina sighed even deeper at Suelle's words than before.

Indeed, Suelle didn't have combat skills. However, Tina knew
the greatness of Suelle, who had gained enough strength to
join the hero party from scratch without any skills.

"The artificers you've created have become the foundation
for all the artificers used in the world now."

"More importantly, as a practical matter, it's doubtful we
could have defeated the Demon Lord without your
artificers—I've told you this many times."
"You seem to not quite understand that."

Tina understood what she wanted to say, but it wasn't that
Suelle was being modest.

The fighting prowess of Tina and the others that Suelle had
witnessed up close as part of the hero party was indeed
extraordinary.

First of all, Tina and her companions could detect attacks
from all directions as if it were natural. And such a thing
was impossible for Suelle with his normal combat abilities.

However, Suelle, who had been acting together with the hero
party, was exposed to situations where he never knew when an
attack might come.

So, what should one do if they are surrounded by powerhouses
like Tina who can detect attacks from all directions?

The answer is simple. Stay still and rigid, and try not to
get in the way as much as possible.

As a result of various actions during the journey to defeat
the Demon Lord, it was embarrassingly clear that this was
the best strategy.

Perhaps because of such experiences, no matter how much his
support was said to be useful, it was always Tina and the
others who actually fought, and Suelle keenly felt his own
powerlessness by witnessing it up close.
"Oops, we've been talking for a bit too long."

"Before more monsters appear, let's head back to town for
now."

Nearby the map are blue and red crystals, which exert their
effects when you approach and press the decision key.

\C[1]Blue\C[0]   Fully restores allies' HP and MP.
\C[2]Red\C[0]   Transitions to reminiscence mode. Pubic hair
toggle

Also, clicking on the character's speech bubble icon during
map actions will give you hints about your next objective.

If you're unsure what to do next, please make use of this
feature.
